BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vQ8qb0qvfFWcK79MohrIB
SUMMARY:Beyond Mysticism: The Modern Northwest
DTSTAMP:20260318T235001Z
DTSTART:20260325T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:image: Drift No. 2\, 1936\, Malcolm M. Roberts\, American\, 191
	3-1990\, tempera on board\, 25 1/2 x 20 5/8 in.\, Seattle Art Museum\, Eug
	ene Fuller Memorial Collection\, 37.103\, © Malcolm M. Roberts\, photo: Sc
	ott Leen.\n\nInspired by the region’s natural beauty and rapidly changing 
	city\, this exhibition showcases artists who told the raw story of Seattle
	 in the 20th century. By sharing the Pacific Northwest’s perspective throu
	gh trending art styles—including Social Realism\, Surrealism\, and Abstrac
	t Expressionism—these artists offered a unique take on Modernist art and c
	hallenged the “mystic” label ascribed to their works.\n\nSpearheading the 
	movement were local icons Mark Tobey\, Kenneth Callahan\, Guy Anderson\, a
	nd Morris Graves—but the range and breadth of Pacific Northwest art goes b
	eyond the “Big Four” of the Northwest School. Featuring more than 150 piec
	es\, this exhibition showcases works that investigate the complexities of 
	daily life in the region. Whether applying an ecocritical lens or producin
	g dreamy and uncanny visuals\, these artists expressed the duality of the 
	natural world and city life to warn of the environmental and social impact
	s of industrialization.\n\nFrom Malcolm Roberts to Kenjiro Nomura\, learn 
	how Northwest artists applied their regional perspective to broader artist
	ic developments to create a new form of American Modernism.\n\nThe exhibit
	ion is accompanied by a fully illustrated catalogue authored by Theresa Pa
	panikolas\, SAM’s Ann M. Barwick Curator of American Art.\n\nhttps://seato
	day.6amcity.com/events/#/details/beyond-mysticism-the-modern-northwest/183
	08126/2026-03-25T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/beyond-mysticism-the-mode
	rn-northwest/18308126/2026-03-25T00
LOCATION:Seattle Art Museum\, 1300 First Avenue\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:p2IIs9E0bTdTODXdgBrHM
SUMMARY:Sturtevant's Ski-Ya-Later Sale: Up to 50% Off Ski and SnowboardGear
DTSTAMP:20260318T235001Z
DTSTART:20260325T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:PNW skiers and snowboarders—spring is the smartest time to upgr
	ade! Sturtevant's \\(part of Christy Sports\\) is hosting the annual Ski-Y
	a-Later Sale from March 6-29\, offering up to 50% off current-season skis\
	, snowboards\, boots\, bindings\, apparel\, and more—perfect as spring sto
	rms bring late-season conditions and families plan ahead during spring bre
	ak.\n\nShop in-person at our Bellevue locations for expert tuning & repair
	\, custom boot fitting\, water sports rentals\, and more: Sturtevant's – 1
	3131 NE 20th St.\, Bellevue\, WA 98005 \\(425.869.7669\\) Hours: Mon-Fri 1
	0 am-7 pm\, Sat-Sun 10 am- 6 pm\n\nSturtevant's Ski Mart – 13219 NE 20th S
	t.\, Bellevue\, WA 98005 \\(425.637.8958\\) Hours: Mon-Fri 10 am-7 pm\, Sa
	t-Sun 10 am-6 pm\n\nOr head to Tacoma: Sturtevant's Ski Mart – 2220 So. 37
	th St.\, Tacoma\, WA 98409 \\(253.473.1134\\) Hours: Mon-Fri 10 am-7 pm\, 
	Sat-Sun 10 am-6 pm.\n\nGreat for families: Stop by for kids' fit checks\, 
	season rental info\, and early purchases before fall pricing. All discount
	ed items are final sale\; selection varies by store. Also shop online at c
	hristysports.com or sturtevants.com. Upgrade your gear locally this spring
	—visit Sturtevant's Bellevue or Tacoma today.\n\nDates: March 6 – March 29
	\, 2026 \\(Progressive discounts: Up to 30% off March 6-12 with the best s
	election\; up to 40% off March 13-19\; up to 50% off March 20-29 for the d
	eepest savings\\)\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/sturtev
	ant-s-ski-ya-later-sale-up-to-50-off-ski-and-snowboardgear/18276036/2026-0
	3-25T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/sturtevant-s-ski-ya-later
	-sale-up-to-50-off-ski-and-snowboardgear/18276036/2026-03-25T00
LOCATION:Sturtevant's Ski Mart\, 13219 NE 20th St.\, Bellevue\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT8H
